for file in files:
    df = pd.read_csv("./Sales_data/" + file)
    all_months_data = pd.concat([all_months_data, df])

def get_state(address):
    x=address.split(',')[1]  #Splitting at first occurance of comma
    y=address.split(',')[2]  #Splitting at Second occurance of comma
    return(x + " " + y)

all_months_data['city'] = all_months_data['Purchase Address'].apply(lambda x:get_state(x))

def get_state(address):
    x=address.split(',')[1]  #Splitting at first occurance of comma
    y=address.split(',')[2].split(' ')[1]  #Splitting at Second occurance of comma
    return(x + " " + y)

def get_city(address):
    return address.split(",")[1] #Split on Comma ans return the item at index 1

def get_state(address):
    return address.split(",")[2].split(' ')[1] #Split on Comma ans return the item at index 1


all_months_data['city'] = all_months_data['Purchase Address'].apply(lambda x: f"{get_city(x)} ({get_state(x)})")

  • The Other items sold the most are Lightening Charging Cables , USB-C Charging Cables, AA betteries
  • Why will that be more than the Washing machines ....well the immediate reaction I have is, because those items are cheap.

  • But as Data Scientist , we would want to prove our hypothesis

So to prove our hypothesis , we could overlay this graph with may be the Actual prices of these items and see if there is a Direct Correlation.

#I'm going to plot a Sub-plot
#We can copy and paste the same Code
#Here instead of x and y , we will use our data 
# x= products , y1 = quantity_ordered , y2 = prices

prices = all_months_data.groupby('Product').mean()['Price Each']

fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()

ax2 = ax1.twinx()
ax1.bar(products, quantity_ordered, color='g')
ax2.plot(products, prices, 'b-')

ax1.set_xlabel('Product Name')
ax1.set_ylabel('Quantity Ordered', color ='g')
ax2.set_ylabel('Price ($)', color='b')
ax1.set_xticklabels(products, rotation = 'vertical', size = 8)

plt.show()

So, if the Price and Quantiy Ordered Kind of correlates then we kind of Prove our Hypothesis

  • Whenever the Quantity orederd is high , the Price should be low
  • We see that , it is the case for AAA and AA batteries
  • Then you can look at some inconsitencies as well.
  • You can say the Price is very high for the Macbook Pro Laptop , then why is the Quantity Ordered so much higher than the LG dryr and Washing machine.
  • Well, there is more demand for MAC Book PRO
